  <rdf:Description rdf:about="http://example.org/mathkg/gloss/IsometricEmbedding">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://example.org/mathkg/GlossRecord"/>
    <rdfs:label>Isometric embedding gloss record</rdfs:label>
    <mathkg:canonicalGloss>Isometric embedding: Let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$.</mathkg:canonicalGloss>
    <mathkg:conciseForm>Isometric embedding: Let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$.</mathkg:conciseForm>
    <mathkg:documentRoleForm>In a mathematical document, isometric embedding usually signals a scalar concept with provenance from OntoMathPRO.</mathkg:documentRoleForm>
    <mathkg:domainTag>general-mathematics</mathkg:domainTag>
    <mathkg:expertForm>Isometric embedding denotes let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$.</mathkg:expertForm>
    <mathkg:glossForConcept rdf:resource="http://example.org/mathkg/Isometricembedding"/>
    <mathkg:pedagogicalForm>Think of isometric embedding as let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$.</mathkg:pedagogicalForm>
    <mathkg:sourceProvenance>OntoMathPRO</mathkg:sourceProvenance>
    <mathkg:sourceProvenanceNote>Selected from OntoMathPRO English-labeled class inventory to complete the 500 target concept layer.</mathkg:sourceProvenanceNote>
    <dcterms:source rdf:resource="http://cll.niimm.ksu.ru/ontologies/mathematics#E1350"/>
    <skos:prefLabel>Isometric embedding</skos:prefLabel>
  </rdf:Description>
